  <main>
    <header class="text-center my-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-blue-600 underline">Laser Refractive Surgery</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mt-2">Achieve Clearer Vision Through Advanced Technology</p>
    </header>

    <section class="container mx-auto p-4 space-y-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <img src="/public/img/lasik.svg" alt="Laser Eye Surgery" class="mx-auto rounded-lg shadow-lg">
      </div>
      <br>

      <article class="space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-blue-500">Overview</h2>
        <p class="text-lg">
          <span class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Laser refractive surgery</span> stands as a modern marvel, offering a pathway to clearer vision and a life liberated from the constraints of glasses and contact lenses. This advanced procedure effectively corrects common refractive issues like myopia, hyperopia, and astigmatism, making it a popular choice for those seeking visual freedom.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-blue-500">Key Benefits</h2>

        <ul class="list-disc pl-8 space-y-2">
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Improved Vision Clarity:</span> Laser eye surgery significantly enhances vision clarity, with many patients achieving 20/20 vision or better post-procedure. By reshaping the cornea, the surgery corrects how light enters the eye, reducing or eliminating blurred vision.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Quick Recovery:</span> Procedures like LASIK offer a swift recovery, with many patients noticing improved vision within hours and resuming normal activities within 24 to 48 hours. The use of local anesthetic eye drops ensures comfort during the procedure, while the quick healing process minimizes downtime.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Reduced Dependence on Eyewear:</span> A major advantage is the reduced dependence on glasses or contact lenses, offering greater convenience and freedom, especially for those with active lifestyles or demanding professions.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Long-Lasting Results:</span> The effects of laser eye surgery are generally permanent. Once the corneal tissue is reshaped, most patients enjoy stable vision for many years, although age-related changes may occur later in life.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Safe and Proven:</span> Laser eye surgery is a well-established and safe medical procedure. Advances in technology, such as femtosecond laser technology used in LASIK, have enhanced the precision and safety of these surgeries.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-blue-500">Types of Laser Refractive Surgery</h2>

        <ul class="list-disc pl-8 space-y-2">
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-blue-600">LASIK:</span> The most frequently performed laser eye surgery that reshapes the cornea to correct refractive errors.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Femto LASIK:</span> A type of LASIK that employs a femtosecond laser for more precise and safer flap creation compared to traditional LASIK.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-blue-600">PRK:</span> A procedure refined with customized treatments like topography-guided PRK, allowing for individualized plans based on corneal characteristics.
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="font-semibold text-blue-600">SMILE (Small Incision Lenticule Extraction):</span> A newer procedure that expands the range of treatable refractive errors while improving safety and predictability.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-blue-500">Conclusion</h2>
        <p class="text-lg">
          Laser refractive surgery offers a range of benefits, from improved vision clarity to reduced dependence on glasses. With advanced technology and safety protocols in place, this procedure remains a trusted option for those seeking freedom from refractive errors.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>
